This paper focuses on optimizing hardware for molecular dynamics simulations using the GROMACS package. This falls under the category of computational science and engineering (cs.CE) as well as numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the performance of different compute nodes, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or software engineering (cs.SE) depending on the specific focus. Finally, the paper involves benchmarking and optimization, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MS) as well.
